news.title: Bengaluru: BBMP mulls action on officials for failure to recover property tax dues
news.para: According to BBMP sources, Munish Moudgil, special commissioner for revenue, submitted a report to the civic body’s chief commissioner Tushar Giri Nath on Jan 30, recommending disciplinary action against revenue officials who have failed to recover property tax from top defaulters in the Bommanahalli zone.

news.title: Over 84,000 apply for regularization under Gunthewari Act
news.para: NMRDA comprises Hingna, Mouda, Kamptee, Nagpur rural, Parsheoni and some villages of Kuhi, Umred, Kalmeshwar and Saoner, A senior NMRDA official said the deadline for submission of online applications ended on January 31. An appeal was made to those who submitted online applications to give their documents in person at the divisional office.

news.title: PMAY beneficiaries in Raipur protest, accuse RMC of 'cheating'
news.para: The residents — Ghanshyam Sahu, Sattu Panka, and housing society president Suraj Yadav — told TOI that most of the PMAY beneficiaries have been allotted old flats with no window panels, doors or proper sanitation facilities.

news.title: 296 illegal colonies to be part of sewer network in Delhi by November, chief secy tells NGT
news.para: Chief secretary Naresh Kumar informs National Green Tribunal that 82% of Delhi's sewage is treated, while the rest comes from unauthorised colonies. Out of 1,799 unauthorised colonies, 1,031 are connected to sewage treatment plants.

news.title: Gurugram: 14 illegal houses on EWS plots demolished in DLF 3
news.para: The move came after several complaints registered with the department alleging illegal construction on 60-square yard EWS category plots.

news.title: Mahindra Lifespaces' net profit up 47% in Q3 FY24
news.para: Mahindra Lifespaces' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 88.77 crore in Q3 FY24, a dip of 55.20 per cent from Rs 198.14 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Arvind SmartSpaces inks two pacts for total 340-acre projects in Surat, Ahmedabad
news.para: Of this, the company has inked a pact to undertake a large horizontal multi use golf themed development including plotted and villa project in Surat, with a total estimated area of over 300 acre and a topline potential of Rs 1,100 crores.

news.title: Mumbai: Saisagar Consultant proprietor arrested in cheating case
news.para: Amboli police on Thursday arrested Jayesh Tanna and produced him before the Andheri Metropolitan magistrate court which remanded him to three days police custody.

news.title: Most builders give cold shoulder to Uttar Pradesh relief package on dues
news.para: So far, of the 57 realtors who were in the pool for the package – this doesn’t factor in another 30-odd whose projects are before courts – just 13 have handed over consent letters to Noida Authority, agreeing to the terms.

news.title: Vamsiram Builders alleges misuse of its name in Rs 3,000 crore Mumbai realty projects
news.para: On Friday, Vamsiram Builders lodged a complaint with the registrar of companies (ROC) and the ministry of corporate affairs alleging that its name, logo, project details, address and even clientele have been impersonated by a Mumbai-based group to execute two big-ticket redevelopment projects.

news.title: Zomato founder buys five-acre land in Delhi for Rs 79 crore
news.para: According to documents accessed through CRE Matrix, a real estate data analytics firm, Goyal has bought first 2.5 acre for Rs 29 crore in March 2023 while the second 2.5 acre land is bought for Rs 50 crore in September 2023.

news.title: State minister for housing urges transparent practices in affordable housing tenders
news.para: Manoj Joshi, secretary, ministry of housing and urban affairs, said that the central government is encouraging all states to increase state property tax, as per the recommendation of the 15th Finance Commission.

news.title: LIC Housing Finance's profit more than double to Rs 1,163 crore in Q3 FY24
news.para: LIC Housing Finance's total income increased to Rs 6,792 crore during the quarter under review against Rs 5,876 crore in the same period last year, LIC Housing Finance said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: RBI imposes Rs 5 lakh penalty on Bajaj Housing Finance
news.para: The penalty has been imposed for contravention of certain provisions of the 'Non-Banking Financial Company - Housing Finance Company (Reserve Bank) Directions, 2021', it said.

news.title: Indiabulls Housing's Rs 3,693 crore rights issue to open on February 7
news.para: The issue price is fixed at Rs 150 per share, having a face value of Rs 2, meaning the issue comes at a premium of Rs 148 per share, the company said in a statement.

news.title: Delhi HC dismisses plea seeking investigation into alleged illegalities by Indiabulls Housing
news.para: ​​A bench headed by Justice Suresh Kumar Kait said there was no merit in the public interest litigation (PIL) filed by NGO 'Citizens Whistle Blower Forum' and the allegations were not supported with evidence.

news.title: Aadhar Housing Finance files Rs 5,000 crore IPO papers with Sebi
news.para: ​The IPO is a combination of a fresh issue of equity shares worth Rs 1,000 crore and an offer-for-sale (OFS) component of Rs 4,000 crore by promoter BCP Topco VII Pte Ltd, an affiliate of Blackstone Group Inc, according to the Draft Red Herring Prospectus (DRHP) filed on Wednesday.

news.title: Senior citizens must not suffer due to stalled redevelopment of residential buildings: Bombay HC
news.para: M/s Square One Realty was appointed to construct a new building, but the builder was unable to start work due to financial troubles.

news.title: Mhalunge-Maan scheme awaits Maharashtra government nod since 2018
news.para: The project was launched in 2018 by then chief minister and the current deputy chief minister Devendra Fadnavis. Officials expect final clearance for the project in the next two months, just ahead of the announcement for the 2024 Lok Sabha polls this year.

news.title: Development rights of Sabarmati riverfront plots up for grabs at lower cost
news.para: The Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation (AMC) made the surprising decision to offer development rights for riverfront plots at significantly lower rates than many areas in western Ahmedabad, including plots recently sold by the AMC. The move has raised eyebrows as the Prahladnagar Multilevel Parking Complex plot was evaluated at Rs 4.03 lakh per sq m last year.
